{"id":15967,"title":"Implementation of a symptomatic approach leads to increased efficiency of a cholera treatment unit.","abstract":"Cholera is a disease of poverty that remains prevalent in resource-limited countries. The abrupt emergence of an epidemic frequently takes communities and health systems by surprise. Spread is rapid and initial mortality high: delays in organizing an appropriate response, lack of health worker training, and high patient numbers contribute to high rates of complications and deaths. ","date":"2014-09-04","categories":"Bacterial Infections and Mycoses","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25092822","annotations":[{"name":"Poverty","weight":0.818686,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poverty"},{"name":"Health","weight":0.781524,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Health"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.750455,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Disease","weight":0.705743,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease"},{"name":"Cholera","weight":0.701447,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cholera"},{"name":"Patient","weight":0.669249,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient"},{"name":"Health care provider","weight":0.667093,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Health_care_provider"},{"name":"Training","weight":0.522715,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Training"},{"name":"Health system","weight":0.522715,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Health_system"},{"name":"Country","weight":0.489597,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Country"},{"name":"Death","weight":0.482455,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Death"},{"name":"Epidemic","weight":0.363126,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Epidemic"},{"name":"Workforce","weight":0.298818,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Workforce"},{"name":"Community","weight":0.101782,"wi